 slightly used and in good condition to ensure the well-being of those using the gear. You can donate gear to SOS by sending or dropping-off donations at any of our offices. When we receive your donation, we will mail you a donation receipt. We accept new or slightly used summer and winter gear â€“ we have particular needs for youth sized outerwear and camping equipment.[/vc_involvedcolumnelement][vc_involvedcolumnelement title=\"Event Donations\" cols=\"two\"]SOS holds many fundraising events throughout the year. In-kind donations can be used for prizes in raffles, student of the month rewards, graduation gifts, the Annual Friends of SOS Pledge Campaign and food or drink assistance for events.[/vc_involvedcolumnelement][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"section bg-white\"][vc_column el_class=\"container\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"row\"][vc_sectiontitleelement title=\"Volunteer\"]There are many volunteer opportunities on and off the mountain with SOS. In fact, over 1000 adult volunteers give their time to SOS each year! We have opportunities for volunteers in outdoor youth programs, special events, as well as volunteer positions in youth mentoring and administrative support. If you are interested, please read on for short descriptions and send an email with your name, location and program of interest to.[/vc_sectiontitleelement][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_involvedvolunteerelement][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Get Involved', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'get-involved', '', '', '2018-06-12 18:06:50', '2018-06-12 18:06:50', '', 0, 'http://sos.juancieridev.tk/?page_id=22', 0, 'page', '', 0),
